Complete this function:

```rust
fn parse_port(input: &str) -> Result<u16, std::num::ParseIntError> {
    // ...
}
```

```rust
fn parse_port(input: &str) -> Result<u16, std::num::ParseIntError> {
    input.trim().parse::<u16>()
}
```

The function trims whitespace and returns the parser result directly.

Complete a function that returns only even numbers from a slice.

```rust
fn even_numbers(values: &[i32]) -> Vec<i32> {
    // ...
}
```

```rust
fn even_numbers(values: &[i32]) -> Vec<i32> {
    values.iter().copied().filter(|value| value % 2 == 0).collect()
}
```

`copied` turns `&i32` items into `i32` values before collection.
